<title>SINGAPORE: BATS sees difficult 1997 market.</title>
<headline>BATS sees difficult 1997 market.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-03-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>British-American Tobacco Company (Singapore) Ltd (BAT) said on Friday it expected the Singapore market to remain difficult in 1997.</p>
<p>&quot;The domestic market is expected to remain difficult with volumes being affected by continuing government anti-smoking policies,&quot; BAT said in a statement accompanying its 1996 results.</p>
<p>It said demand for off-shore trading and services might show some improvement but contract manufacturing would continue to to be volatile due to competitive pressures.  </p>
<p>BAT reported its 1996 net profit slipped three percent to Singapore $31.85 million on a turnover of S$329.54 million.</p>
<p>--Singapore newsroom (65-8703080)</p>
